---
title: "St. Louis Blues History"
output: html_document
---

The franchise was founded in 1967 as one of the six teams from the 1967 NHL expansion and is named after the W. C. Handy song *Saint Louis Blues*. The Blues qualified for the playoffs in all but nine of their 52 seasons, appeared in the Stanley Cup Finals four times, and won the Stanley Cup in 2019. 
